# VentureNode — Cursor Rules

# Project Overview
VentureNode is an autonomous multi-agent AI system for startup operations, built for the Notion MCP Challenge.
Backend: Python / FastAPI / LangGraph. Frontend: Next.js 14 / Tailwind / Shadcn UI.

# Rules: Always Follow

## Architecture Constraints
- Notion is the exclusive data store. Do NOT introduce PostgreSQL, SQLite, or MongoDB.
- All agent logic must live in `backend/agents/`. One file per agent.
- All Notion operations must go through `backend/notion/mcp_client.py`. Agents must not call the Notion SDK directly.
- The LangGraph graph is defined exclusively in `backend/orchestrator/graph.py`.

## API Constraints
- Use ONLY free APIs: Groq (LLM), DuckDuckGoSearchRun (OSINT), FAISS (Memory).
- Do NOT suggest SerpApi, OpenAI, Pinecone, Weaviate, or any paid service.
- All API keys are read from environment variables via `backend/core/config.py`.

## Code Quality Standards
- Python: PEP 8 compliant. All functions typed. Google-style docstrings required.
- TypeScript: Strict mode. No `any` types. Use Server Components where possible.
- No placeholders. No `TODO` comments. No `pass` statements in production code.

## Frontend Standards
- Use `lucide-react` for all icons. Prefer Shadcn UI component primitives.
- Use Framer Motion for all transitions and micro-animations.
- All Tailwind only. No inline styles. No custom CSS unless absolutely necessary.

## Security Standards
- Never suggest hardcoding API keys in source code.
- CORS must be restricted in production builds.
